President Donald Trump delivered remarks during the commissioning ceremony of the USS Gerald R. Ford, a new aircraft carrier for the United States Navy. He praised the men and women of the Navy, and emphasized the importance of American military might and the need for a strong defense. Trump also called for an increase in defense spending and the expansion of the Navy fleet. He highlighted the historic significance of the ship and the legacy of former President Gerald Ford, for whom the carrier is named. Trump expressed his commitment to supporting the military and ensuring the safety and security of the nation.